## Build The Web App

```bash
cd web
pnpm install
trunk build --release
```

## Run The Backend

From the workspace root:

```bash
cargo run -p {{ workspace.backend_crate_name }}
```

Then open:

- `http://127.0.0.1:3000{{ app.mount_path }}`

Useful endpoints:

- `http://127.0.0.1:3000/healthz`
- `http://127.0.0.1:3000{{ backend.metadata_path }}`

## Notes

- This is a generated MVP Studio app.
- The backend is the production server.
- Trunk is only the build tool for the Yew frontend.
- Tailwind CSS and DaisyUI are wired into the generated web app.
- Metadata browsing works without the upstream service.
- Model list requests require the upstream service to be reachable and may still require real auth or signed-request support depending on the target service.
